information_schema Structure (Quick Reference)

Database → Tables → Columns

In MySQL metadata:

information_schema
     │
     ├── tables
     │      ├── table_schema  → database name
     │      └── table_name    → table name
     │
     └── columns
            ├── table_name    → table name
            └── column_name   → column name

---

Full Enumeration Flow

database()
      ↓
information_schema.tables
      ↓
table_name
      ↓
information_schema.columns
      ↓
column_name
      ↓
SELECT column FROM table

---

Visual Flow

 Database
    ↓
  Tables
    ↓
  Columns
    ↓
   Data

Example attack path:

database() → academy_labs
table_name → users
column_name → username,password
data → SELECT username,password FROM users
